<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-190-050 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 368 387</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacUser  April 1991 v7 n4 p87(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Darwin's Dilemma. (Software Review) (Inline Design)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Breen, Christopher.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   ALP Software Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Darwin's Dilemma (Computer game)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     EvaluationComputer gamesSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Darwin's DilemmaandM;&quot;I used to be a better swimmer, but I outgrew it, thanks to...evolution.&quot;andO;Emo Phillips would have felt right at home with Darwin's Dilemma, where, asthe saying goes, the solution is evolution.andM;The setup is simple.andP;  The play window is made up of an invisible 9 x 6 gridon which reside icons representing life is simple to complex forms, startingwith the lowly amoeba and progressing through different game levels toself-actualized Man.andP;  You are provided with a game piece, named Darwin, whoseonly purpose is to shove the icons in one of the four compass directions.andO;You shove these icons either to position them or to combine them with likeicons.andP;  An example: Your window contains, among other things, four amoebas.andO;If properly combined, they become, through theprocess of evolution, a singleparamecium.andP;  Position Darwin to bang the paramecia together, and you get ajellyfish.andP;  Jellyfish become octopi, octopi become crabs, and you're on yourway.andP;  A technique called teleswapping lets you shift icons from one locationon the grid to another, but beware: Teleswaps are limited.andM;That's all there is to it.andP;  Darwin's Dilemma is easy to play but difficult towin.andP;  To play Darwin's Dilemma properly, you need to plan several moves inadvance and use your teleswaps judiciously.andP;  Yes, you can undo as many as 120moves, but it costs points.andP;  Then again, points seem to be of little concernin this game.andP;  In Darwin's Dilemma, it's strictly survival of the fittest.andO;Highly recommended for those who enjoy pondering and puzzling.andM;Inline Design, 5 W. Mountain Road, Sharon, CT 06069andgt; (20) 364-0063.andP;  Version1.0 $49.95.andO;</TEXT></DOC>